{"lemma":"ظَلامٌ","slug":"ظَلامٌ","root":"ظ.ل.م","root_slug":"ظ-ل-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ظ-ل-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ظَلامٌ","root":"ظلم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":5},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27651","n27652","n27653","n27658","n27659"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B8%D9%8E%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"darkness, gloom","tags":["uncountable"],"examples":[{"text":"بينما ذهب بعض من مستخدمي مواقع التواصل الاجتماعي إلى أن فتح الصندوق ورفع الغطاء سيصيب العالم بلعنة، حيث سيؤدي ذلك إلى أن يسود الظلام العالم، وسيغطي على ضوء الشمس مما سيجعل الأرض تعيش في ظلام دامس لمدة 1000 عام تقريبا."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"oppressor, tyrant","examples":[{"text":"مَنْ عَمِلَ صَالِحًا فَلِنَفْسِهِ وَمَنْ أَسَاءَ فَعَلَيْهَا وَمَا رَبُّكَ بِظَلَّامٍ لِلْعَبِيدِ"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"evildoer"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Akkadian 𒈪 (ṣalmum, “black, dark”) and Biblical Hebrew צַלְמָוֶת (ṣalmɔ́wɛṯ, “deep shadow”)."},"ipa":["/ðˤa.laːm/","/ðˤal.laːm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27651","headword_ar":"ظَلَامٌ","root":"Zlm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZulomapN","text_ar":"ظُلْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27652","headword_ar":"ظُلَامٌ","root":"Zlm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, in the first quarter of the paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27653","headword_ar":"ظِلَامٌ","root":"Zlm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, near the beginning:       -A2-  see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~aAmN","text_ar":"ظِلَّامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-  It signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Little,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small, in quantity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mean, contemptible, paltry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of no weight"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b2-  whence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naZara A_ilaY~a","text_ar":"نَظَرَ اـِلَىَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZilaAmFA","text_ar":"ظِلَامًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$azorFA","text_ar":"شَزْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He looked at me from the outer angle of the eye, with anger,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aversion"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27658","headword_ar":"ظَلَّامٌ","root":"Zlm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~iymN","text_ar":"ظِلِّيمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaluwmN","text_ar":"ظَلُومٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned in the M and K with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaAlimN","text_ar":"ظَالِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as though syn. therewith, but it is an intensive epithet,] One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who acts wrongfully, unjustly, injuriously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tyrannically, much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"often; i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaviyru AlZ~ulomi","text_ar":"كَثِيرُ الظُّلْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~aAmuwna lilojuzuri","text_ar":"ظَلَّامُونَ لِلْجُزُرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in a verse of Ibn-Mukbil [meaning (assumed tropical:)  Men"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"often slaughtering camels without disease"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T, S.)       -A2